Last Broadcast Date: Thu 17 Jun 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Lucy Ash. Story of the life and death of Neda Agha-Soltan; Nepal's mountain investigator Elizabeth Hawley. Neda Agha-Soltan How exiled Iranian journalist Saeed Kamali Dehghan made the risky journey home to film a documentary about the life of Neda Agha-Soltan, the young woman shot dead during Iran's Green Revolution last year. "For Neda" is a Mentorn Media production for HBO. You can download it at Elizabeth Hawley Outlook goes to Katmandu to meet the redoubtable Miss Hawley, who makes sure mountaineers are telling the truth about reaching the summit. Show less